snippet.textDisplay:
The Australian Falun Dafa Association and Vietnamese Community in Australia NSW Chapter held a joint rally on Sydney Town Hall Square on December 10, 2019, Human Rights Day. Fourteen people spoke during the rally and condemned the Chinese Communist Party’s (CCP) persecution of Falun Gong practitioners, Vietnamese, Uighur, Tibetan, and Hong Kong people.

They called on the Australian Government to pass legislation similar to the Global Magnitsky Human Rights Accountability Act in the U.S. to sanction human rights perpetrators. Falun Gong practitioners demonstrated the five sets of exercises before the rally, and talked to passersby about the CCP’s persecution.
